<style>
  #content {font: inherit;vertical-align: baseline;color: #555;font-size: 14px;line-height: 24px;float: right;position: relative;margin: 0 18px 0 0;border: 1px solid #CCCCCC;padding: 10px;border-radius: 8px;;width: 640px;}
  .top-heading {padding:10px 0 !important;line-height: 50px;}
  #content img {border: 1px solid #ccc;padding: 5px;border-radius: 7px;margin: 6px 0 0 0;}
</style>
<%= render :partial=>"/integrations/instructions_left_menu" %>
<div id="content">
  <h1 class="top-heading">Integrate UsersDelight with Shopify Store</h1>

  <p>Helps Shopify customers to increase conversions using Notification, gain customer insights using Survey and have customer support up and running within few seconds using Feedback.</p>

  <div class="content-section-data">
    <p>If you are not signed up with UsersDelight already, you'll need to do so. Please sign up and create a widget for
      your Shopify store first. <a href="/pricing">Select a plan and sign-up</a> now.</p>

    <p>Follow these steps to add UsersDelight integration code to your store:</p>

    <h2>1. Go to Shopify store's control panel and click on "Themes &gt; Template Editor"</h2>
    <div class="we-thumbnail-container" align="center">
      <img src="//d3701cc9l7v9a6.cloudfront.net/images/v1/platform/shopify-1.jpg" height="286" width="600" alt="Shopify UsersDelight Integration Step 1"/>
      <div class="caption">Login to your store's control panel and click "Themes &gt; Template Editor"
        link in header navigation</div>
    </div>

    <h2>2. Browse layout themes</h2>
    <p>On the left hand side, you would see Layouts section. Click on the layout that you use. By default, you would see a layout named  'theme.liquid'. On clicking your theme, its HTML markup will appear on the right hand side. Scroll-down to the bottom of the markup section.</p>
    <div class="we-thumbnail-container" align="center">
      <img src="//d3701cc9l7v9a6.cloudfront.net/images/v1/platform/shopify-2.jpg" height="324" width="600" alt="Shopify UsersDelight Integration Step 2"/>
      <div class="caption">Go to store "Template Editor &gt; Layouts &gt; Themes".</div>
    </div>

    <h2>3. Copy-paste UsersDelight integration code into "Themes" and save the file</h2>
    <p> Paste the integration code just before the end of the body tag (<i>&lt;/body&gt;</i>)</p>
    <div class="we-thumbnail-container" align="center">
      <img src='/images/webcode.png'/>
      <div class="caption">Get it from UsersDelight Dashboard &gt; Website Campaigns &gt; Add website</div>
    </div>

    <p>
      That's it! Your Shopify store is now UsersDelight ready. You can customize your Feedback options, create
      new Surveys and new Notifications in your UsersDelight Dashboard. No code changes are needed on your store.
    </p>
    Note: SSL support is only available for customers subscribed to the <a href="/pricing">Basic plan</a> or higher.
  </div>
</div>